# {{projectName}}

Performance test suite built with [k6](https://k6.io/) by Grafana Labs.

## Prerequisites

- [k6](https://k6.io/docs/getting-started/installation/) installed locally
- Node.js {{toolVersions.node}} (for npm scripts)

## Quick Start

```bash
# Run load test
k6 run scripts/load-test.js

# Run stress test
k6 run scripts/stress-test.js

# Run with HTML report output
k6 run --out json=results/output.json scripts/load-test.js
```

## Test Types

| Script | Purpose | Duration |
|--------|---------|----------|
| `load-test.js` | Simulates normal expected load | ~5 min |
| `stress-test.js` | Pushes beyond normal capacity | ~10 min |
| `spike-test.js` | Sudden surge of traffic | ~5 min |
| `soak-test.js` | Extended duration for memory leaks | ~30 min |

## Configuration

Edit `config/thresholds.json` to adjust pass/fail thresholds.

